# Repo Hygiene Rules

Canonical spec: `docs/REPO_HYGIENE_SPEC.md`. These rules enforce it at edit time.

## Root directory

Do NOT create files at repo root matching these patterns:
- `FINAL_*`, `QA_*`
- `*_SUMMARY.md`, `*_REPORT.md`, `*_ASSESSMENT.md`, `*_COMPLETION*.md`
- Date-stamped status docs (e.g. `*_20260610.md`)

Approved root files are listed in `config/governance-contract.yaml`
(`repo_hygiene.approved_root_files`). Everything else goes to `docs/`,
`artifacts/`, or `archive/`.

## Generated reports and evidence

All QA reports, research outputs, verification results, and incident evidence
must go into a **dated bundle folder**:

```
artifacts/<domain>/<yyyy-mm-dd>-<slug>/REPORT.md
```

Never place loose files directly under `artifacts/`. Each bundle needs at
minimum `REPORT.md` (or `VERDICT.md`) and `index.md` (or `artifacts.json`).

## Naming

- Do not use status adjectives in filenames: `FINAL`, `COMPLETE`, `LATEST`, `NEW`, `FIXED`.
- Do not create case-variant duplicates (e.g. `Foo_Summary.md` alongside `FOO_SUMMARY.md`).
- Use lowercase kebab-case for evidence bundle slugs.

## Archive

Superseded or historical material goes to `archive/<yyyy-mm-dd>-<reason>/` with
a `README.md` explaining reason, original location, and restore policy.

## Canonical Source Policy

Every document has exactly one canonical location. Secondary copies are only
permitted as generated consumers (written by automation, never edited directly).

## Module Documentation

Every new module must have a contract README at `docs/modules/<module>/README.md`
with sections: What, Why, How, Dependencies, Owner. A new module without a
contract README is a hygiene violation.
